(64, 76, 'en', 'Variables', 'Variables\r\nMost of the time, a JavaScript application needs to work with information. Here are two examples:\r\n\r\nAn online shop – the information might include goods being sold and a shopping cart.\r\nA chat application – the information might include users, messages, and much more.', '<header class=\"main__header\" style=\"margin: 40px 0px 16px; font-family: &quot;system-ui&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><div class=\"main__header-inner\" style=\"\"><h1 class=\"main__header-title\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: auto; padding: 0px; break-after: avoid; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 32px; line-height: 40px; font-family: BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Variables</font></span></h1></div></header><div class=\"content\" style=\"font-family: &quot;system-ui&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><article class=\"formatted\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/TechArticle\" style=\"\"><div itemprop=\"author\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Person\"></div><div itemprop=\"articleBody\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Most of the time, a JavaScript application needs to work with information. Here are two examples:</font></span></p><ol style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 22px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 21px;\"><li style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">An online shop – the information might include goods being sold and a shopping cart.</font></span></li><li style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">A chat application – the information might include users, messages, and much more.</font></span></li></ol><p style=\"margin: 12px 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Variables are used to store this information.</font></span></p><h2 style=\"margin: 24px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-size: 24px; line-height: 32px; font-family: BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; position: relative; break-after: avoid;\"><a class=\"main__anchor\" name=\"a-variable\" href=\"https://javascript.info/variables#a-variable\" style=\"outline: 0px; font: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">A variable</font></a></h2><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; break-before: avoid;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">A&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Variable_(computer_science)\">variable</a>&nbsp;is a “named storage” for data. We can use variables to store goodies, visitors, and other data.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">To create a variable in JavaScript, use the&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">let</code>&nbsp;keyword.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">The statement below creates (in other words:&nbsp;<em>declares</em>) a variable with the name “message”:</font></span></p><div id=\"xnnzcl59ah\" data-trusted=\"1\" class=\"code-example\" data-prism-highlighted=\"1\" style=\"margin: 22px 0px;\"><div class=\"codebox code-example__codebox\" style=\"width: 800px; height: 54px; position: relative; margin: 1.5em 0px 0px; overflow: auto;\"><div class=\"codebox__code\" data-code=\"1\" style=\"width: 800px; height: 54px;\"><pre class=\"line-numbers  language-javascript\" tabindex=\"0\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; width: 800px; height: 54px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; direction: ltr; word-spacing: normal; tab-size: 4; hyphens: none; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; counter-reset: e 0; display: flex; flex-direction: row; z-index: 0; text-shadow: none;\"><span class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"pointer-events: none; width: auto; letter-spacing: -1px; border: 0px; user-select: none; padding: 1em 0px 0.8em; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ;\"><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span></span><code class=\" language-javascript\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-