(65, 77, 'en', 'Data types', 'Data types\r\nA value in JavaScript is always of a certain type. For example, a string or a number.\r\n\r\nThere are eight basic data types in JavaScript. Here, we’ll cover them in general and in the next chapters we’ll talk about each of them in detail.', '<header class=\"main__header\" style=\"margin: 40px 0px 16px; font-family: &quot;system-ui&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><div class=\"main__header-inner\" style=\"\"><h1 class=\"main__header-title\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: auto; padding: 0px; break-after: avoid; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 32px; line-height: 40px; font-family: BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Data types</font></span></h1></div></header><div class=\"content\" style=\"font-family: &quot;system-ui&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><article class=\"formatted\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/TechArticle\" style=\"\"><div itemprop=\"author\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Person\" style=\"\"></div><div itemprop=\"articleBody\" style=\"\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">A value in JavaScript is always of a certain type. For example, a string or a number.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">There are eight basic data types in JavaScript. Here, we’ll cover them in general and in the next chapters we’ll talk about each of them in detail.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">We can put any type in a variable. For example, a variable can at one moment be a string and then store a number:</font></span></p><div id=\"refyh2b5hp\" data-trusted=\"1\" class=\"code-example\" data-prism-highlighted=\"1\" style=\"margin: 22px 0px;\"><div class=\"codebox code-example__codebox\" style=\"width: 800px; height: 98px; position: relative; margin: 1.5em 0px 0px; overflow: auto;\"><div class=\"codebox__code\" data-code=\"1\" style=\"width: 800px; height: 98px;\"><pre class=\"line-numbers  language-javascript\" tabindex=\"0\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; width: 800px; height: 98px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; direction: ltr; word-spacing: normal; tab-size: 4; hyphens: none; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; counter-reset: e 0; display: flex; flex-direction: row; z-index: 0; text-shadow: none;\"><span class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"pointer-events: none; width: auto; letter-spacing: -1px; border: 0px; user-select: none; padding: 1em 0px 0.8em; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ;\"><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span></span><code class=\" language-javascript\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 1em 1em 1em 0.5em; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-radius: 0.3em; z-index: 1; text-shadow: none; margin: 0px; direction: ltr; word-spacing: normal; tab-size: 4; hyphens: none; position: relative; flex-grow: 1;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\"><span class=\"token comment\" style=\"\">// no error</span>\r\n<span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">let</span> message <span class=\"token operator\" style=\"\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\" style=\"\">\"hello\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">;</span>\r\nmessage <span class=\"token operator\" style=\"\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\" style=\"\">123456</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">;</span></font></span></code></pre></div></div></div><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Programming languages that allow such things, such as JavaScript, are called “dynamically typed”, meaning that there exist data types, but variables are not bound to any of them.</font></span></p><h2 style=\"margin: 24px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-size: 24px; line-height: 32px; font-family: BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; position: relative; break-after: avoid;\"><a class=\"main__anchor\" name=\"number\" href=\"https://javascript.info/types#number\" style=\"outline: 0px; font: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Number</font></a></h2><div id=\"k3kb7wnq4a\" data-trusted=\"1\" class=\"code-example\" data-prism-highlighted=\"1\" style=\"margin: 22px 0px;\"><div class=\"codebox code-example__codebox\" style=\"width: 800px; height: 76px; position: relative; margin: 1.5em 0px 0px; overflow: auto;\"><div class=\"codebox__code\" data-code=\"1\" style=\"width: 800px; height: 76px;\"><pre class=\"line-numbers  language-javascript\" tabindex=\"0\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; width: 800px; height: 76px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; direction: ltr; word-spacing: normal; tab-size: 4; hyphens: none; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; counter-reset: e 0; display: flex; flex-direction: row; z-index: 0; text-shadow: none;\"><span class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"pointer-events: none; width: auto; letter-spacing: -1px; border: 0px; user-select: none; padding: 1em 0px 0.8em; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ;\"><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span></span><code class=\" language-javascript\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 1em 1em 1em 0.5em; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-radius: 0.3em; z-index: 1; text-shadow: none; margin: 0px; direction: ltr; word-spacing: normal; tab-size: 4; hyphens: none; position: relative; flex-grow: 1;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\"><span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">let</span> n <span class=\"token operator\" style=\"\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\" style=\"\">123</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">;</span>\r\nn <span class=\"token operator\" style=\"\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\" style=\"\">12.345</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">;</span></font></span></code></pre></div></div></div><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">The&nbsp;<em>number</em>&nbsp;type represents both integer and floating point numbers.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">There are many operations for numbers, e.g. multiplication&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">*</code>, division&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">/</code>, addition&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">+</code>, subtraction&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">-</code>, and so on.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Besides regular numbers, there are so-called “special numeric values” which also belong to this data type:&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">Infinity</code>,&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;,