xt-shadow: none;\"><span class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"pointer-events: none; width: auto; letter-spacing: -1px; border: 0px; user-select: none; padding: 1em 0px 0.8em; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ;\"><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span></span><code class=\" language-javascript\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 1em 1em 1em 0.5em; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-radius: 0.3em; z-index: 1; text-shadow: none; margin: 0px; direction: ltr; word-spacing: normal; tab-size: 4; hyphens: none; position: relative; flex-grow: 1;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\"><span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">let</span> age <span class=\"token operator\" style=\"\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\" style=\"\">100</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">;</span>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"token comment\" style=\"\">// change the value to undefined</span>\r\nage <span class=\"token operator\" style=\"\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">undefined</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">;</span>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"token function\" style=\"\">alert</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">(</span>age<span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\" style=\"\">// \"undefined\"</span></font></span></code></pre></div></div></div><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">…But we don’t recommend doing that. Normally, one uses&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">null</code>&nbsp;to assign an “empty” or “unknown” value to a variable, while&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">undefined</code>&nbsp;is reserved as a default initial value for unassigned things.</font></span></p><h2 style=\"margin: 24px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-size: 24px; line-height: 32px; font-family: BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; position: relative; break-after: avoid;\"><a class=\"main__anchor\" name=\"objects-and-symbols\" href=\"https://javascript.info/types#objects-and-symbols\" style=\"outline: 0px; font: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Objects and Symbols</font></a></h2><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; break-before: avoid;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">The&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">object</code>&nbsp;type is special.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">All other types are called “primitive” because their values can contain only a single thing (be it a string or a number or whatever). In contrast, objects are used to store collections of data and more complex entities.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Being that important, objects deserve a special treatment. We’ll deal with them later in the chapter&nbsp;<a href=\"https://javascript.info/object\">Objects</a>, after we learn more about primitives.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">The&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">symbol</code>&nbsp;type is used to create unique identifiers for objects. We have to mention it here for the sake of completeness, but also postpone the details till we know objects.</font></span></p><h2 style=\"margin: 24px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-size: 24px; line-height: 32px; font-family: BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; position: relative; break-after: avoid;\"><a class=\"main__anchor\" name=\"type-typeof\" href=\"https://javascript.info/types#type-typeof\" style=\"outline: 0px; font: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">The typeof operator</font></a></h2><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; break-before: avoid;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">The&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">typeof</code>&nbsp;operator returns the type of the operand. It’s useful when we want to process values of different types differently or just want to do a quick check.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">A call to&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">typeof x</code>&nbsp;returns a string with the type name:</font></span></p><div id=\"85znmbovmi\" data-trusted=\"1\" class=\"code-example\" data-highlight=\"[{&quot;start&quot;:16,&quot;end&quot;:16},{&quot;start&quot;:14,&quot;end&quot;:14},{&quot;start&quot;:12,&quot;end&quot;:12}]\" data-prism-highlighted=\"1\" style=\"margin: 22px 0px;\"><div class=\"codebox code-example__codebox\" style=\"width: 800px; height: 406px; position: relative; margin: 1.5em 0px 0px; overflow: auto;\"><div class=\"codebox__code\" data-code=\"1\" style=\"width: 800px; height: 406px;\"><pre class=\"line-numbers  language-javascript\" tabindex=\"0\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; width: 800px; height: 406px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; direction: ltr; word-spacing: normal; tab-size: 4; hyphens: none; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; counter-reset: e 0; display: flex; flex-direction: row; z-index: 0; text-shadow: none;\"><span class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"pointer-events: none; width: auto; letter-spacing: -1px; border: 0px; user-select: none; padding: 1em 0px 0.8em; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ;\"><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span></span><code class=\" language-javascript\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 1em 1em 1em 0.5em; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-radius: 0.3em; z-index: 1; text-shadow: none; margin: 0px; direction: ltr; word-spacing: normal; tab-size: 4; hyphens: none; position: relative; flex-grow: 1;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\"><span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">typeof</span> <span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">undefined</span> <span class=\"token comment\" style=\"\">// \"undefined\"</span>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">typeof</span> <span class=\"token number\" style=\"\">0</span> <span class=\"token comment\" style=\"\">// \"number\"</span>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">typeof</span> <span class=\"token number\" style=\"\">10n</span> <span class=\"token comment\" style=\"\">// \"bigint\"</span>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">typeof</span> <span class=\"token boolean\" style=\"\">true</span> <span class=\"token comment\" style=\"\">// \"boolean\"</span>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">typeof</span> <span class=\"token string\" style=\"\">\"foo\"</span> <span class=\"token comment\" style=\"\">// \"string\"</span>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">typeof</span> <span class=\"token function\" style=\"\">Symbol</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">(</span><span class=\"token string\" style=\"\">\"id\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\" style=\"\">// \"symbol\"</span>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"block-highlight\" style=\"display: inline-block; pointer-events: none; line-height: inherit; width: 726.109px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ;\"><span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">typeof</span> Math <span class=\"token comment\" style=\"\">// \"object\"  (1)</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"block-highlight\" style=\"display: inline-block; pointer-events: none; line-height: inherit; width: 726.109px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ;\"><span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">typeof</span> <span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">null</span> <span class=\"token comment\" style=\"\">// \"object\"  (2)</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"block-highlight\" style=\"display: inline-block; pointer-events: none; line-height: inherit; width: 726.109px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ;\"><span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">typeof</span> alert <span class=\"token comment\" style=\"\">// \"function\"  (3)</span></span></font></span></code></pre></div></div></div><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">The last three lines may need additional explanation:</font></span></p><ol style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 22px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 21px;\"><li style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\"><code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">Math</code>&nbsp;is a built-in object that provides mathematical operations. We will learn it in the chapter&nbsp;<a href=\"https://javascript.info/number\">Numbers</a>. Here, it serves just as an example of an object.</font></span></li><li style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">The result of&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">typeof null</code>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">\"object\"</code>. That’s an officially recognized error in&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">typeof</code>, coming from very early days of JavaScript and kept for compatibility. Definitely,&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">null</code>&nbsp;is not an object. It is a special value with a separate type of its own. The behavior of&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">typeof</code>&nbsp;is wrong here.</font></span></li><li style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">The result of&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">typeof alert</code>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">\"function\"</code>, because&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">alert</code>&nbsp;is a function. We’ll study functions in the next chapters where we’ll also see that there’s no special “function” type in JavaScript. Functions belong to the object type. But&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">typeof</code>&nbsp;treats them differently, returning&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">\"function\"</code>. That also comes from the early days of JavaScript. Technically, such behavior isn’t correct, but can be convenient in practice.</font></span></li></ol><div class=\"important important_smart\" style=\"margin: 16px 0px; border: 3px solid var(--borderImportant); border-radius: 6px;\"><div class=\"important__header\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 24px 24px 0px; border: none;\"><span class=\"important__type\" style=\"font-weight: 700; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">The&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">typeof(x)</code>&nbsp;syntax</font></span></div><div class=\"important__content\" style=\"margin: 12px 24px 24px;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">You may also come across another syntax:&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">typeof(x)</code>. It’s the same as&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">typeof x</code>.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">To put it clear:&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">typeof</code>&nbsp;is an operator, not a function. The parentheses here aren’t a part of&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">typeof</code>. It’s the kind of parentheses used for mathematical grouping.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Usually, such parentheses contain a mathematical expression, such as&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">(2 + 2)</code>, but here they contain only one argument&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">(x)</code>. Syntactically, they allow to avoid a space between the&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">typeof</code>&nbsp;operator and its argument, and some people like it.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Some people prefer&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">typeof(x)</code>, although the&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">typeof x</code>&nbsp;syntax is much more common.</font></span></p></div></div><h2 style=\"margin: 24px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-size: 24px; line-height: 32px; font-family: BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; position: relative; break-after: avoid;\"><a class=\"main__anchor\" name=\"summary\" href=\"https://javascript.info/types#summary\" style=\"outline: 0px; font: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Summary</font></a></h2><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; break-before: avoid;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">There are 8 basic data types in JavaScript.</font></span></p><ul style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 22px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 21px; list-style: none;\"><li style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Seven primitive data types:</font></span><ul style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 21px; list-style: none;\"><li style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\"><code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">number</code>&nbsp;for numbers of any kind: integer or floating-point, integers are limited by&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">±(2<sup>53</sup>-1)</code>.</font></span></li><li style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\"><code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">bigint</code>&nbsp;for integer numbers of arbitrary length.</font></span></li><li style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\"><code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">string</code>&nbsp;for strings. A string may have zero or more characters, there’s no separate single-character type.</font></span></li><li style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\"><code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">boolean</code>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">true</code>/<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">false</code>.</font></span></li><li style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\"><code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">null</code>&nbsp;for unknown values – a standalone type that has a single value&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">null</code>.</font></span></li><li style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\"><code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">undefined</code>&nbsp;for unassigned values – a standalone type that has a single value&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">undefined</code>.</font></span></li><li style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\"><code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">symbol</code>&nbsp;for unique identifiers.</font></span></li></ul></li><li style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">And one non-primitive data type:</font></span><ul style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 21px; list-style: none;\"><li style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\"><code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">object</code>&nbsp;for more complex data structures.</font></span></li></ul></li></ul><p style=\"margin: 12px 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">The&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">typeof</code>&nbsp;operator allows us to see which type is stored in a variable.</font></span></p><ul style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 22px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 21px; list-style: none;\"><li style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Usually used as&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">typeof x</code>, but&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">typeof(x)</code>&nbsp;is also possible.</font></span></li><li style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Returns a string with the name of the type, like&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">\"string\"</code>.</font></span></li><li style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">For&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">null</code>&nbsp;returns&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">\"object\"</code>&nbsp;– this is an error in the language, it’s not actually an object.</font></span></li></ul><p style=\"margin: 12px 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">In the next chapters, we’ll concentrate on primitive values and once we’re familiar with them, we’ll move on to objects.</font></span></p></div></article></div>');
