(67, 79, 'en', 'Type Conversions', 'Type Conversions\r\nMost of the time, operators and functions automatically convert the values given to them to the right type.\r\n\r\nFor example, alert automatically converts any value to a string to show it. Mathematical operations convert values to numbers.\r\n\r\nThere are also cases when we need to explicitly convert a value to the expected type.', '<header class=\"main__header\" style=\"margin: 40px 0px 16px; font-family: &quot;system-ui&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><div class=\"main__header-inner\" style=\"\"><h1 class=\"main__header-title\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: auto; padding: 0px; break-after: avoid; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 32px; line-height: 40px; font-family: BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Type Conversions</font></span></h1></div></header><div class=\"content\" style=\"font-family: &quot;system-ui&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><article class=\"formatted\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/TechArticle\" style=\"\"><div itemprop=\"author\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Person\" style=\"\"></div><div itemprop=\"articleBody\" style=\"\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Most of the time, operators and functions automatically convert the values given to them to the right type.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">For example,&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">alert</code>&nbsp;automatically converts any value to a string to show it. Mathematical operations convert values to numbers.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">There are also cases when we need to explicitly convert a value to the expected type.</font></span></p><div class=\"important important_smart\" style=\"margin: 16px 0px; border: 3px solid var(--borderImportant); border-radius: 6px;\"><div class=\"important__header\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 24px 24px 0px; border: none;\"><span class=\"important__type\" style=\"font-weight: 700; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Not talking about objects yet</font></span></div><div class=\"important__content\" style=\"margin: 12px 24px 24px;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">In this chapter, we won’t cover objects. For now, we’ll just be talking about primitives.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Later, after we learn about objects, in the chapter&nbsp;<a href=\"https://javascript.info/object-toprimitive\">Object to primitive conversion</a>&nbsp;we’ll see how objects fit in.</font></span></p></div></div><h2 style=\"margin: 24px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-size: 24px; line-height: 32px; font-family: BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; position: relative; break-after: avoid;\"><a class=\"main__anchor\" name=\"string-conversion\" href=\"https://javascript.info/type-conversions#string-conversion\" style=\"outline: 0px; font: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">String Conversion</font></a></h2><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; break-before: avoid;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">String conversion happens when we need the string form of a value.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">For example,&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">alert(value)</code>&nbsp;does it to show the value.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">We can also call the&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">String(value)</code>&nbsp;function to convert a value to a string:</font></span></p><div id=\"ytig9i5h8z\" data-trusted=\"1\" class=\"code-example\" data-highli