 rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">string</font></code></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Whitespaces (includes spaces, tabs&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px; font-weight: inherit;\">\\t</code>, newlines&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px; font-weight: inherit;\">\\n</code>&nbsp;etc.) from the start and end are removed. If the remaining string is empty, the result is&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px; font-weight: inherit;\">0</code>. Otherwise, the number is “read” from the string. An error gives&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px; font-weight: inherit;\">NaN</code>.</font></span></td></tr></tbody></table><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 