 background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-radius: 0.3em; z-index: 1; text-shadow: none; margin: 0px; direction: ltr; word-spacing: normal; tab-size: 4; hyphens: none; position: relative; flex-grow: 1;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\"><span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">let</span> apples <span class=\"token operator\" style=\"\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\" style=\"\">\"2\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">;</span>\r\n<span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">let</span> oranges <span class=\"token operator\" style=\"\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\" style=\"\">\"3\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">;</span>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"token function\" style=\"\">alert</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">(</span> apples <span class=\"token operator\" style=\"\">+</span> oranges <span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\" style=\"\">// \"23\", the binary plus concatenates strings</span></font></span></code></pre></div></div></div><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">If we want to treat them as numbers, we need to convert and then sum them:</font></span></p><div id=\"dqmubyrwd1\" data-trusted=\"1\" class=\"code-example\" data-highlight=\"[{&quot;start&quot;:3,&quot;end&quot;:4}]\" data-prism-highlighted=\"1\" style=\"margin: 22px 0px;\"><div class=\"codebox code-example__codebox\" style=\"width: 800px; height: 208px; position: relative; margin: 1.5em 0px 0px; overflow: auto;\"><div class=\"toolbar codebox__toolbar\" style=\"position: absolute; top: 0px; right: 0px; z-index: 9; opacity: 0.8; display: table-row;\"><div class=\"toolbar__tool\" style=\"display: table-cell; padding-left: 1px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\"><a href=\"https://javascript.info/operators#\" title=\"run\" data-action=\"run\" class=\"toolbar__button toolbar__button_run\" style=\"padding: 0px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; display: inline-block; vertical-align: bottom; width: 30px; height: 30px; text-align: center; line-height: 30px;\"></a></font></span></div><div class=\"toolbar__tool\" style=\"display: table-cell; padding-left: 1px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\"><a href=\"https://javascript.info/operators#\" title=\"open in sandbox\" target=\"_blank\" data-action=\"edit\" class=\"toolbar__button toolbar__button_edit\" style=\"padding: 0px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; display: inline-block; vertical-align: bottom; width: 30px; height: 30px; text-align: center; line-height: 30px;\"></a></font></span></div></div><div class=\"codebox__code\" data-code=\"1\" style=\"width: 800px; height: 208px;\"><pre class=\"line-numbers  language-javascript\" tabindex=\"0\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; width: 800px; height: 208px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; direction: ltr; word-spacing: normal; tab-size: 4; hyphens: none; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; counter-reset: e 0; display: flex; flex-direction: row; z-index: 0; text-shadow: none;\"><span class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"pointer-events: none; width: auto; letter-spacing: -1px; border: 0px; user-select: none; padding: 1em 0px 0.8em; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ;\"><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span></span><code class=\" language-javascript\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 1em 1em 1em 0.5em; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-radius: 0.3em; z-index: 1; text-shadow: none; margin: 0px; direction: ltr; word-spacing: normal; tab-size: 4; hyphens: none; position: relative; flex-grow: 1;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\"><span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">let</span> apples <span class=\"token operator\" style=\"\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\" style=\"\">\"2\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">;</span>\r\n<span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">let</span> oranges <span class=\"token operator\" style=\"\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\" style=\"\">\"3\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">;</span>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"block-highlight\" style=\"display: inline-block; pointer-events: none; line-height: inherit; width: 726.109px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ;\"><span class=\"token comment\" style=\"\">// both values converted to numbers before the binary plus</span>\r\n<span class=\"token function\" style=\"\">alert</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">(</span> <span class=\"token operator\" style=\"\">+</span>apples <span class=\"token operator\" style=\"\">+</span> <span class=\"token operator\" style=\"\">+</span>oranges <span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\" style=\"\">// 5</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"token comment\" style=\"\">// the longer variant</span>\r\n<span class=\"token comment\" style=\"\">// alert( Number(apples) + Number(oranges) ); // 5</span></font></span></code></pre></div></div></div><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">From a mathematician’s standpoint, the abundance of pluses may seem strange. But from a programmer’s standpoint, there’s nothing special: unary pluses are applied first, they convert strings to numbers, and then the binary plus sums them up.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Why are unary pluses applied to values before the binary ones? As we’re going to see, that’s because of their&nbsp;<em>higher precedence</em>.</font></span></p><h2 style=\"margin: 24px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-size: 24px; line-height: 32px; font-family: BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; position: relative; break-after: avoid;\"><a class=\"main__anchor\" name=\"operator-precedence\" href=\"https://javascript.info/operators#operator-precedence\" style=\"outline: 0px; font: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Operator precedence</font></a></h2><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; break-before: avoid;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">If an expression has more than one operator, the execution order is defined by their&nbsp;<em>precedence</em>, or, in other words, the default priority order of operators.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">From school, we all know that the multiplication in the expression&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">1 + 2 * 2</code>&nbsp;should be calculated before the addition. That’s exactly the precedence thing. The multiplication is said to have&nbsp;<em>a higher precedence</em>&nbsp;than the addition.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Parentheses override any precedence, so if we’re not satisfied with the default order, we can use them to change it. For example, write&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">(1 + 2) * 2</code>.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">There are many operators in JavaScript. Every operator has a corresponding precedence number. The one with the larger number executes first. If the precedence is the same, the execution order is from left to right.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Here’s an extract from the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/Operator_Precedence\">precedence table</a>&nbsp;(you don’t need to remember this, but note that unary operators are higher than corresponding binary ones):</font></span></p><table style=\"width: 800px; font-size: 15px; margin: 30px 0px;\"><thead><tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid var(--borderPrimary);\"><th style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px; border-bottom: 3px solid var(--borderPrimary); vertical-align: bottom;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Precedence</font></span></th><th style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px; text-align: left; border-bottom: 3px solid var(--borderPrimary); vertical-align: bottom;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Name</font></span></th><th style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px; text-align: left; border-bottom: 3px solid var(--borderPrimary); vertical-align: bottom;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Sign</font></span></th></tr></thead><tbody style=\"border: 0px;\"><tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid var(--borderPrimary);\"><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">…</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">…</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">…</font></span></td></tr><tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid var(--borderPrimary); background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ;\"><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">14</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">unary plus</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; border-radius: 2px; font-weight: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">+</font></code></td></tr><tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid var(--borderPrimary);\"><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">14</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">unary negation</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; border-radius: 2px; font-weight: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">-</font></code></td></tr><tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid var(--borderPrimary); background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ;\"><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">13</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">exponentiation</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; border-radius: 2px; font-weight: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">**</font></code></td></tr><tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid var(--borderPrimary);\"><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">12</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">multiplication</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; border-radius: 2px; font-weight: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">*</font></code></td></tr><tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid var(--borderPrimary); background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ;\"><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">12</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">division</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; border-radius: 2px; font-weight: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">/</font></code></td></tr><tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid var(--borderPrimary);\"><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">11</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">addition</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; border-radius: 2px; font-weight: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">+</font></code></td></tr><tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid var(--borderPrimary); background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ;\"><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">11</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">subtraction</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; border-radius: 2px; font-weight: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">-</font></code></td></tr><tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid var(--borderPrimary);\"><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">…</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">…</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">…</font></span></td></tr><tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid var(--borderPrimary); background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ;\"><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">2</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">assignment</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; border-radius: 2px; font-weight: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">=</font></code></td></tr><tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid var(--borderPrimary);\"><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">…</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">…</font></span></td><td style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 1em 2px 5px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">…</font></span></td></tr></tbody></table><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">As we can see, the “unary plus” has a priority of&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">14</code>&nbsp;which is higher than the&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">11</code>&nbsp;of “addition” (binary plus). That’s why, in the expression&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">\"+apples + +oranges\"</code>, unary pluses work before the addition.</font></span></p><h2 style=\"margin: 24px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-size: 24px; line-height: 32px; font-family: BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; position: relative; break-after: avoid;\"><a class=\"main__anchor\" name=\"assignment\" href=\"https://javascript.info/operators#assignment\" style=\"outline: 0px; font: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Assignment</font></a></h2><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; break-before: avoid;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Let’s note that an assignment&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">=</code>&nbsp;is also an operator. It is listed in the precedence table with the very low priority of&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">2</code>.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">That’s why, when we assign a variable, like&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">x = 2 * 2 + 1</code>, the calculations are done first and then the&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">=</code>&nbsp;is evaluated, storing the result in&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">x</code>.</font></span></p><div id=\"kcok6qylk8\" data-trusted=\"1\" class=\"code-example\" data-prism-highlighted=\"1\" style=\"margin: 22px 0px;\"><div class=\"codebox code-example__codebox\" style=\"width: 800px; height: 98px; position: relative; margin: 1.5em 0px 0px; overflow: auto;\"><div class=\"codebox__code\" data-code=\"1\" style=\"width: 800px; height: 98px;\"><pre class=\"line-numbers  language-javascript\" tabindex=\"0\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; width: 800px; height: 98px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; direction: ltr; word-spacing: normal; tab-size: 4; hyphens: none; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; counter-reset: e 0; display: flex; flex-direction: row; z-index: 0; text-shadow: none;\"><span class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"pointer-events: none; width: auto; letter-spacing: -1px; border: 0px; user-select: none; padding: 1em 0px 0.8em; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ;\"><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span><span style=\"pointer-events: none; display: block; counter-increment: e 1;\"></span></span><code class=\" language-javascript\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 1em 1em 1em 0.5em; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-radius: 0.3em; z-index: 1; text-shadow: none; margin: 0px; direction: ltr; word-spacing: normal; tab-size: 4; hyphens: none; position: relative; flex-grow: 1;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\"><span class=\"token keyword\" style=\"\">let</span> x <span class=\"token operator\" style=\"\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\" style=\"\">2</span> <span class=\"token operator\" style=\"\">*</span> <span class=\"token number\" style=\"\">2</span> <span class=\"token operator\" style=\"\">+</span> <span class=\"token number\" style=\"\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">;</span>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"token function\" style=\"\">alert</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">(</span> x <span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\" style=\"\">// 5</span></font></span></code></pre></div></div></div><h3 style=\"margin: 30px 0px 22px; padding: 0px; font-size: 20.48px; line-height: 24.576px; position: relative; break-after: avoid;\"><a class=\"main__anchor\" name=\"assignment-returns-a-value\" href=\"https://javascript.info/operators#assignment-returns-a-value\" style=\"outline: 0px; font: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Assignment = returns a value</font></a></h3><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; break-before: avoid;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">The fact of&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">=</code>&nbsp;being an operator, not a “magical” language construct has an interesting implication.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">All operators in JavaScript return a value. That’s obvious for&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">+</code>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">-</code>, but also true for&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">=</code>.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">The call&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">x = value</code>&nbsp;writes the&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">value</code>&nbsp;into&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">x</code>&nbsp;<em>and then returns it</em>.</font></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Here’s a demo that uses an assignment as part of a more complex expression:</font></span></p><div id=\"i6j0motdsd\" data-trusted=\"1\" class=\"code-example\" data-highlight=\"[{&quot;start&quot;:3,&quot;end&quot;:3}]\" data-prism-highlighted=\"1\" style=\