(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Important:</font></span></div><div class=\"important__content\" style=\"margin: 12px 24px 24px;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">Increment/decrement can only be applied to variables. Trying to use it on a value like&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">5++</code>&nbsp;will give an error.</font></span></p></div></div><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">The operators&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">++</code>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<code style=\"font-family: Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, Menlo, Monaco, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; background-image: ; background-position-x: ; background-position-y: ; background-size: ; background-repeat-x: ; background-repeat-y: ; background-attachment: ; background-origin: ; background-clip: ; border-radius: 2px;\">--</code>&nbsp;can be placed either before or after a variable.</font></span></p><ul style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 22px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 21px; list-style: none;\"><li style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">When the operator goes after th